msgstr "Os endpoints com escopo `@Singleton` e `@ApplicationScoped` sĂŁo compartilhados entre todas as conexĂľes WebSocket. Portanto, as implementaĂ§Ăľes devem ser sem estado ou Ă  prova de threads."

#. type: Title ===
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/websockets-next-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Session context"
msgstr "Contexto da sessĂŁo"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/websockets-next-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If an endpoint is annotated with `@SessionScoped`, or depends directly or indirectly on a `@SessionScoped` bean, then each WebSocket connection is associated with its own _session context_.\n"
"The session context is active during endpoint callback invocation.\n"
"Subsequent invocations of <<callback-methods>> within the same connection utilize the same session context.\n"
"The session context remains active until the connection is closed (usually when the `@OnClose` method completes execution), at which point it is terminated."
msgstr "Se um endpoint for anotado com `@SessionScoped` ou depender direta ou indiretamente de um bean `@SessionScoped` , cada conexĂŁo WebSocket serĂĄ associada ao seu prĂłprio _contexto de sessĂŁo_ . O contexto de sessĂŁo permanece ativo durante a invocaĂ§ĂŁo do callback do endpoint. As invocaĂ§Ăľes subsequentes de ` <<callback-methods>> ` dentro da mesma conexĂŁo utilizam o mesmo contexto de sessĂŁo. O contexto de sessĂŁo permanece ativo atĂŠ que a conexĂŁo seja encerrada (geralmente quando o mĂŠtodo `@OnClose` conclui sua execuĂ§ĂŁo), momento em que ĂŠ encerrado."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.34/guides/websockets-next-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "It is also possible to set the `quarkus.websockets-next.server.activate-session-context` config property to `always`. In this case, the session context is always activated, no matter if a `@SessionScoped` bean participates in the dependency tree."
msgstr "TambĂŠm ĂŠ possĂ­vel definir a propriedade de configuraĂ§ĂŁo ` `quarkus.websockets-next.server.activate-session-context` ` como ``always`` . Nesse caso, o contexto de sessĂŁo fica sempre ativado, independentemente de haver ou nĂŁo um bean com `o` escopo ``@SessionScoped`` na ĂĄrvore de dependĂŞncias."

